ELEVENLABS AGENT CONFIG (Mercy ConvAI):
- After large edits to the agent or tools, run `node scripts/fetch-agent.js` once (requires `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` in `.env.local`) to refresh `agent_configs/Mercy-AI-Agent-LIVE.json` from the API so `tool_id` values match the live workspace.
- Then apply workflow-only changes locally and deploy. This prevents local JSON from drifting from live tool IDs.
- To push the edited LIVE file back to the workspace without script mutations, run `node scripts/push-live-agent.js` (same API key). Run `node scripts/validate-workflow-edges.js` before pushing to ensure LLM edges keep labels and conditions.
- ElevenLabs workflow debugger UI sometimes shows "EMPTY STRING" on a condition column that does not map to API `forward_condition.condition` for LLM edges (legacy/expression slot). Trust the JSON. Breadcrumbs like `Mercy AI AgentBooking Request` come from concatenating a display title with the node label without a separator; end `name`, `phone_numbers[].assigned_agent.agent_name`, and `platform_settings.widget.text_contents.main_label` with ` — ` (em dash, the widget label is often what the debugger uses). For workflow node titles, avoid a leading em dash on the node `label` if the agent title already ends with ` — `, so the breadcrumb does not show a double dash.